On Fri, 13 Jul 2007, Jeffrey Hendery wrote:

> The Haynes manual talks about using a tyre lever to relieve residual tension
> in the torsion bar.  After a quick search on the internet it looks like this
> tool is used to remove tires from wheels.  Anyone had experience with a tyre
> lever or other tools used to relieve the torsion bar tension?

For this application, tire lever = really big screwdriver.

When I did mine there wasn't much tension on it.  I could have lifted it
off the stop with my hand.
